# No + Prefix for Non-Route Files

In SvelteKit, **files whose names start with `+` are reserved** for framework route/layout files (e.g. `+page.svelte`, `+page.server.ts`, `+layout.server.ts`). Only SvelteKit’s own conventions may use the `+` prefix.

## Rule

- **Do not** create or rename any file so that its name starts with `+` (e.g. `+page.server.test.ts`, `+layout.server.test.ts`).
- Test files that target route modules must **not** use the `+` prefix. Place them next to the route and use a name without `+`.

## Examples

| Avoid (reserved)     | Use instead              |
|----------------------|--------------------------|
| `+page.server.test.ts`   | `page.server.test.ts`   |
| `+layout.server.test.ts` | `layout.server.test.ts` |

Imports from the actual route modules are unchanged (e.g. `import { load } from './+page.server'`), because the **source** file is still `+page.server.ts`; only the **test** file name must not start with `+`.
